article.headline: Villarroel sparks Sooners' rally, finishes with 18 points
article.linkText: No. 18 Oklahoma needs late run to put away Wichita State
article.story:
WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- Maria Villarroel scored 18 points, and Oklahoma (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today; No. 15 Associated Press) was unable to shake Wichita State until the
final minutes of a 70-64 victory Monday night.

	   Oklahoma (7-2), which trailed 34-30 at halftime, never really
took control of the game until the final 3:20, when it outscored
Wichita State (4-2), 12-4.

	   Wichita State was led by Carlesa Dixon with 17 points.

	   The Shockers held their last lead at 45-44, with 13:33 left when
Dixon made two free throws.

	   After Dixon scored from inside but missed a free throw,
Villarroel hit two free throws with 36.9 seconds remaining to give
Oklahoma a 67-62 lead.

	   The Sooners sank six free throws down the stretch -- five by
Villarroel. She also scored on a fastbreak with 2:20 left to gave
Oklahoma a 65-60 lead.

	   The Sooners got 15 points from Dionnah Jackson, 13 from Teresa
Schuknecht and 12 from Chelsi Welch.

	   Raeven King added 13 points and Angela Buckner 12 for the
Shockers.
